<section class="light-theme">
    <div class="inner-section">

        <img class="lazy" src="/assets/images/lizAndAidanPlaceholder.svg" data-src="/assets/images/lizAndAidan.jpg" alt="Picture of UVM Votes members carving pumpkins.">

        <h2 class="title" data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="zoom-out" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">The Issue.</h2>
        <div class="non-flex-wrapper">
            <figure class="highcharts-figure">
                <div id="container"></div>
            </figure>
        </div>
        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Compared with other universities around the country, our voting rate is down. This on top of the fact that the underrepresentation of college students is experienced widely across the country, not to mention how that compounds with issues of socio-economic status. According to
            <a class="link" href="assets/General-Election-NSLVE-Data.pdf" target="_blank">our campus report</a>
            from the National Study of Learning, Voting, and Education, less than half of UVM's undergraduate students voted in the last general election.</p>

        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back" class="bold">We can fix this.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-theme">
    <div class="inner-section mission">
        <h2 class="title" data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="zoom-out" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Our Solution</h2>
        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">We're helping folks plan to vote with
            <em>pumpkin-to-student</em>
            direct marketing. This essentially looks like carving pumpkins with voting inspired slogans or faces and placing them around campus with QR codes mounted on top (which link to voter resources). Also, we're going to flyer campus with Got Milk styled profiles and chalk up the ground around campus. If that sounds fun, then for the love of peat,
            <a class="link" href="#sign-up">do it with us!</a>
        </p>
        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Although we focused on student texting earlier, now we're pivoting to register any remaining students in-state, making the process as easy as possible.
        </p>
        <div class="roles-wrapper">
            <div data-sal="fade" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back" class="role">
                <h3>Volunteer</h3>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/user-plus-solid.svg" %}
                    <h4>Register</h4>
                    <div>Make sure folks are registered to vote, no matter where they are.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/tasks-solid.svg" %}
                    <h4>Prepare</h4>
                    <div>No one should risk their life to vote; we'll share resources for voting early or by mail.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/vote-yea-solid.svg" %}
                    <h4>Get out the vote!</h4>
                    <div>We'll follow through until Election Day, encouraging everyone to be heard before the polls close on November 3rd.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div data-sal="fade" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back" class="role">
                <h3>Organize</h3>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/hands-helping-solid.svg" %}
                    <h4>Recruit</h4>
                    <div>Before helping students vote, we need as many volunteers as possible.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/life-ring-regular.svg" %}
                    <h4>Support</h4>
                    <div>Help coordinate volunteers before and during our three contact sessions.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="description">
                    {% include "svgs/chalkboard-teacher-solid.svg" %}
                    <h4>Educate</h4>
                    <div>If students ask volunteers questions they don't know the answer to, you'll jump in and help out.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="sign-up">
            <form name="Role request" method="POST" data-netlify="true" data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="zoom-in" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">
                <h3>Get Involved!</h3>
                <div class="user-box">
                    <input type="text" name="name" required=""/>
                    <label>Email:</label>
                </div>
                <div class="form-bottom">
                    <div class="quick-fix-thanks">
                        <label>
                            <input type="radio" name="interest" value="Volunteer" checked="checked">
                            Volunteer
                        </label>
                        <label>
                            <input type="radio" name="interest" value="Organize">
                            Organize
                        </label>
                    </div>
                    <button class="link-btn" type="submit">Submit</button>
                </div>

            </form>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>
</section>

<section class="light-theme">
<div class="inner-section" id="greater-vision">
    <h2 class="title" data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="zoom-out" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">The Greater Vision</h2>
    <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Institutionalize voting.</p>

    <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Our Student Government Association signed off on the
        <a class="link" href="https://www.evcnational.org/blogpost/jumpstarting-our-campus-presence-with-time-off-to-vote" target="_blank">Time Off To Vote letter</a>, but UVM as an institution is really well positioned to do more for helping students vote.</p>

    <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">One of the easiest changes would be including voter registration tables at events like Orientation Day and adding a button to voter resources into the myUVM portal. More involved options also include giving election day off or encouraging students to consider their voter status during class sign-ups (Stanford is trying
        <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://www.stanforddaily.com/2020/02/06/new-enrollment-hold-encourages-students-to-register-to-vote/">that idea</a>
        right now).</p>

    <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">We also know that
        <a target="blank" class="link" href="https://vtcynic.com/news/a-gerrymandered-student-ward-how-burlingtons-ward-8-got-its-shape/">Ward 8 is a gerrymandered district</a>
        overrepresenting students, so why not move polling to the Davis Center?</p>
</div>
</section>

